#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:1
msgid "CMake package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:4
msgid "releng-tool now populates `CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:7
msgid ""
"A CMake package provides support for processing a [CMake][cmake] "
"supported module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:14
msgid ""
"During the configuration stage of a CMake package, `cmake` will be "
"invoked to generate build files for the module. For the build stage, "
"`cmake --build` will invoke the generated build files. Similar approach "
"for the installation stage where the build option is invoked again but "
"with the `install` target invoked: `cmake --build --target install`. Each"
" stage can be configured to manipulate environment variables and options "
"used by the CMake executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:21
msgid ""
"The default configuration built for projects is `RelWithDebInfo`. A "
"developer can override this option by explicitly adjusting the "
"configuration option `LIBFOO_CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE` to, for example, `Debug`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:29
msgid ""
"Packages can be configured with a toolchain using with the define "
"[`CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE`][cmake-toolchain-file] (via [`LIBFOO_CONF_DEFS"
"`](pkg-opt-cmake-conf-defs)) or using the command line option "
"[`--toolchain`][cmake-opt-toolchain] (via [`LIBFOO_CONF_OPTS`](pkg-opt-"
"cmake-conf-opts)). releng-tool will provide required staging/target paths"
" through the [`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH`][cmake-find-root-path] "
"configuration. Ensure the toolchain configuration accepts "
"`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH` hints. For example, using either:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:43
msgid "Or:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:51
msgid ""
"The following shows the default arguments used in stages and outlines "
"configuration options that are available for an CMake package to set. See"
" also the [CMake package examples](/examples/examples-cmake). All stages "
"are invoked with a [`PKG_BUILD_DIR`](env-pkg-build-dir) working "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:61
msgid "Configuration stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:64
msgid "The configuration stage invokes `cmake` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:70
msgid "With the configuration cache that populates the options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:85
msgid ""
"The project directory is configured to [`PKG_BUILD_DIR`](env-pkg-build-"
"dir)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:87
msgid ""
"The build type is configured by [`LIBFOO_CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE`](pkg-opt-"
"cmake-build-type)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:90
msgid ""
"Paths may vary based on how the package's [`LIBFOO_INSTALL_TYPE`](pkg-"
"opt-install-type) is configured. System root paths provided will only "
"include the staging directory if `staging` is configured. Both the "
"staging and target directories are provided is the `target` is "
"configured. Likewise with the host directory if `host` is configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:96
msgid ""
"The same concepts apply for defined include "
"(`<sysroot>[/<prefix>]/include`), library (`<sysroot>[/<prefix>]/lib`) "
"and module paths (`<sysroot>[/<prefix>]/share/cmake/Modules`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:100
msgid ""
"Packages may override default defines using the [`LIBFOO_CONF_DEFS`](pkg-"
"opt-cmake-conf-defs) option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:103
msgid ""
"A package may opt-out of configuring "
"`CMAKE_<LANG>_STANDARD_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES` variables using the "
"[`releng.cmake.disable_direct_includes`](quirk-"
"releng.cmake.disable_direct_includes) quirk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:114
msgid "Build stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:117
msgid "The build stage invokes `cmake` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:123
#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:159
msgid "With the following environment variables set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:129
#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:166
msgid ""
"The `--build` directory is configured to [`PKG_BUILD_OUTPUT_DIR`](env-"
"pkg-build-output-dir)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:132
#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:169
msgid ""
"The `--config` type is configured to the value defined for "
"[`LIBFOO_CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE`](pkg-opt-cmake-build-type). Although, this "
"option may not be applicable/used in all build environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:136
msgid ""
"The environment variable `CMAKE_BUILD_PARALLEL_LEVEL` is populated by "
"either the [`--jobs` argument](arg-jobs), [`LIBFOO_FIXED_JOBS`](pkg-opt-"
"fixed-jobs) or [`LIBFOO_MAX_JOBS`](pkg-opt-max-jobs). Although, if the "
"configuration results in a single job, the environment variable will not "
"be set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:147
msgid "Install stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:150
msgid "The install stage invokes `cmake` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:173
msgid ""
"The `DESTDIR` path will be set to the target sysroot the package should "
"install into (see also [`LIBFOO_INSTALL_TYPE`](pkg-opt-install-type)). "
"`cmake` may be invoked multiple times for each target it needs to install"
" into."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-cmake.md:177
msgid ""
"The installation stage can be skipped by configuring "
"[`LIBFOO_CMAKE_NOINSTALL`](pkg-opt-cmake-noinstall)."
msgstr ""

